\f1\b\fs28 \cf0 Statistical Analysis\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs24 \cf0 Continuous variables were expressed as mean \'b1 standard deviation, and categorical variables as percentages. Group comparisons were performed using analysis of variance or chi-square tests as appropriate. Multivariate linear regression analyses were used to assess associations between smartphone use, sleep quality, and cardiometabolic outcomes. Mediation analysis was conducted to evaluate the role of sleep quality. A p-value < 0.05 was considered statistically significant.\
