\f1\b\fs36 \cf0 \strokec2 Discussion\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs24 \cf0 This study demonstrates a significant association between excessive smartphone use, poor sleep quality, and early cardiometabolic risk markers in young adults. Participants with higher daily smartphone use exhibited poorer sleep quality and evidence of metabolic dysregulation, even in the absence of overt disease.\
The findings suggest that sleep disruption may serve as a key mechanism linking smartphone use to adverse metabolic outcomes. Blue light exposure, delayed bedtime, and increased cognitive arousal may collectively impair sleep architecture, leading to hormonal and metabolic disturbances such as increased cortisol levels and insulin resistance.\
The observed elevation in hs-CRP among high smartphone users indicates the presence of low-grade inflammation, which has been implicated in the pathogenesis of cardiovascular disease and metabolic syndrome. Although young adults typically have low absolute cardiometabolic risk, early subclinical changes may have long-term consequences if unhealthy behaviors persist.\
Strengths of this study include comprehensive assessment of sleep and metabolic markers and adjustment for multiple lifestyle factors. Limitations include the cross-sectional design, reliance on self-reported smartphone use, and inability to establish causality.\
Longitudinal studies are needed to determine whether reducing smartphone use and improving sleep hygiene can reverse metabolic abnormalities and reduce future cardiometabolic risk.\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf3 \strokec3 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa298\partightenfactor0

\f1\b\fs36 \cf0 \strokec2 Conclusion\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs24 \cf0 Excessive smartphone use is associated with poor sleep quality and early indicators of cardiometabolic risk in young adults. These findings highlight the importance of promoting healthy digital habits and sleep hygiene as part of preventive health strategies in younger populations.\
